Package: survalis
Type: Package
Title: Interpretable and Causal Machine Learning Methods for Survival
        Analysis
Version: 0.6.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Imad", family = "El Badisy",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "elbadisyimad@gmail.com")
)
Description: A modular toolkit for interpretable and causal survival machine learning. 
    Includes many built-in learners (e.g., statistical models, tree-based models, deep leanring models) and supports 
    user-defined models that return time-indexed survival 
    probability matrices. Provides model-agnostic interpretability methods such as SHAP, 
    PDP, ALE, surrogate models, feature importance, and counterfactual explanations. Designed to integrate 
    seamlessly via a unified fit and predict interface.
